ns:common.topic.description: OBJ3 is a version of OBJ based on order-sorted rewriting. OBJ3 is agent-oriented and runs on Kyoto Common Lisp AKCL. It is now of historical interest since newer versions of the OBJ family are available.

ns:common.document.text: OBJ3 is a version of OBJ based on order-sorted rewriting. OBJ3 is agent-oriented and runs on Kyoto Common Lisp AKCL. It is now of (important) historical interest since newer versions of the OBJ family are available.\nThis article was originally based on material from the Free On-line Dictionary of Computing, which is licensed under the GFDL.
